                 <br>
                  The Forum can be easily customised on-line through configuration 
                  files that allow you to turn on or off e-mail notification, 
                  add or amend Forum categories, set the colour, font, font size, 
                  etc. of the Forum to suite your web site, and change the administration 
                  username and password.<br>
                    <br>
                  The Forum displays Topics in order of how recently a Reply has 
                  been added to the Topic with the time, date, and author of the 
                  last post in that particular Topic. Also the Forum displays 
                  how many views each Topic has received and how many Replies 
                  there are within the Topic. <br>
                    <br>
                    The e-mail notification can be setup so that you can be informed 
                    each time a post is posted in the Forum and/or a user can 
                    be informed by e-mail if someone posts a reply to there Topic.<br>
                    <br>
                    The Forum can also show programming code such as ASP or HTML, 
                    keeping it's original structure, making ideal for Forum's 
                    on programing subjects as well as just general Discussion 
                    Forum's.<br>
                    <br>
                  There are many advanced features included in this Forum that 
                  are normally only found in forums that you have to pay for, 
                  including: - 
                  <ul>
                    <li>Emoticons</li>
                    <li>Message text formatting</li>
                    <li>Images, hyper-links, and e-mail address can be added to 
                      posts </li>
                    <li>Post preview</li>
                    <li>Printer friendly version of posts</li>
                    <li>Message quoting and editing</li>
                    <li>E-mail notification of posts to the thread starter and 
                      forum administrator</li>
                    <li>E-mail forgotten passwords to users</li>
                    <li>E-mail a friend</li>
                    <li>Welcome e-mail sent to new users</li>
                    <li>Support for Microsoft's CDONTS mail component and the 
                      w3 JMail e-mail component</li>
                    <li>Search facilities</li>
                    <li>Members list</li>
                    <li>Auto Login</li>
                    <li>Log-off user</li>
                    <li>Set forum moderators</li>
                    <li>Password protected Administration and Configuration Area</li>
                  </ul>
